The paper proposes a novel approach for multimodal fusion in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep convolutional networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of multi-task learning, which is a technique used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimodal learning (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CL, and cs.AI.
